Time to Upgrade

 
 
 
 
 

Jib 1.0.0 is GA - Building Java Docker Images Has Never Been Easier

Many months ago, we introduced Jib  – an open-source Java containerizer created by Google that lets you build containers using Maven and Gradle with minimal effort.
Version 1.0 ships with support for WAR projects, Integration with Skaffold for Kubernetes and Core API.
Read on to find out more!

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

Eclipse MicroProfile 2.2

Eclipse MicroProfile 2.2 updates the Fault Tolerance, Open Tracing, Open API, and Rest Client APIs and continues to align itself with Java EE 8. It brings some specification clarifications and documentation enhancements and offers a richer integration between MicroProfile APIs. Furthermore, all these APIs offer CDI-based and programmatic easy-to-use interfaces. To find out more about this new release, click the link!

A New JDK12 Stream API Collector

When following major Java releases, we usually focus on bold and controversial JEPs while humble and tiny changes get introduced unnoticeably. One such change is Collectors#teeing in JDK12 which allows the use of two independent Collectors and then merging their results using a BiFunction. Read more to find out how to use it in practice!

Istio Service Mesh, the Step-by-Step Guide

Istio service mesh provides several capabilities for traffic monitoring, access control, discovery, security, resiliency, and other useful things to a bundle of services. It delivers all that and strikingly does not require any changes to the code of any of those services. To make this possible, Istio deploys an Istio proxy (called an Istio sidecar) next to each service. For a more detailed explanation of where it can be used, its capabilities and its architecture, visit this two-part guide!
Part 1: Theory
Part 2: Tutorial

The Best Way to Call a Stored Procedure with JPA and Hibernate

The way Hibernate handles stored procedures can lead to “maximum open cursors exceeded” issues on Oracle. In this article, however, you are going to learn the best way to call a stored procedure when using JPA and Hibernate so that the underlying JDBC resources are released as soon as possible.

 
 
 
 

Configuring Spring Boot with application.properties File

Spring Boot comes with a built-in mechanism for application configuration using a file called application.properties. In some scenarios, however, you may need more flexibility. In this article, you will learn how to create your custom properties, work with primitive and more complex data types inside your application and create separate file dedicated for each of your runtime environments.

 
 
 
 

Vert.x Kotlin Coroutines​

Coroutines are a nice alternative to callback based composition that are available out of the box in Kotlin. Thanks to the Vert.x Kotlin coroutines integration you can use coroutines in Vert.x as well. Jump in the following article to explore how to reap the benefits of it and compose asynchronous functions more easily.

 
 
 

Cloud Programming Simplified: A Berkeley View on Serverless Computing

Serverless cloud computing handles virtually all the system administration operations needed to make it easier for programmers to use the cloud. It provides an interface that greatly simplifies cloud programming, and represents an evolution that parallels the transition from assembly language to high-level programming languages. This paper explains the motivation for serverless computing, describes applications that stretch the current limits of serverless, and then lists obstacles and research opportunities required for serverless computing to fulfill its full potential. Have a good read!
